<@U1JB7QCBD>: you need a linux foundation account <https://identity.linuxfoundation.org/>

<@U0KM61BCP> thanks. May I ask what is the process surrounding the generation of documentation? What should I do if I want stuff fixed in it? (like how certain parts of it still refer to the github repo). Also,  are there maybe docker images with v0.5?
or whatever the current suggested version is.

<@U1JB7QCBD> it is baked into the build. however, when we transitioned to Gerrit, we also had to change how the docs are hosted. Previously, they were hosted by <http://redthedocs.com|redthedocs.com> servers, but they don’t support Gerrit, only GH with webhooks. We currently have an ask in to spin up a server to host all of our docs (fabric and sawtooth) and I hope to have that operational in a couple days. IN the interim, you can use <https://cbf-fabric-docs.readthedocs.io/>
